{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κοσμ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>order, arrange</b>, especially <b>set</b> an army <b>in array, marshal</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.379; κοσμῆσαι ἵππους τε καὶ ἀνέρας 2.554 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ἐπεὶ κόσμηθεν ἅμ᾽ ἡγεμόνεσσιν ἕκαστοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3.1 \">Refs</a>]; πένταχα κοσμηθέντες <b>marshalled</b> in five bodies, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 12.87 \">Refs</a>]; of a population, διὰ τρίχα κοσμηθέντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2.655; once in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”, of hunters, διὰ δὲ τρίχα κοσμηθέντες 9.157:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —<i>middle</i>, κοσμησάμενος πολιήτας <b>having arranged his</b> men, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.806 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so after Homer, κ. στρατόν (variant for{κοιμήσων}) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 662; τάξεις κεκοσμημέναι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.1.26, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 247a; ἐπὶ τάξις πλεῦνας ἐκεκοσμέατο 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.31. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> generally, <b>arrange, prepare</b>, δόρπον ἐκόσμει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.13; κ. ἀοιδήν η “Bacch.” 59; ἔργα 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 306; στέφανον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 74; τράπεζαν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.2.6; εἰς τάφον λέβητα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1401 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, δεῖπνον κεκόσμηται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 1.22 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δεῖ οὕτω κοσμηθῆναι ὅκως.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 266 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; τὸ κοσμηθὲν αἷμα, ={τὸνοἰκεῖον κόσμον κτησάμενον}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 5.551. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>order, rule</b>, τὴν πόλιν κ. καλῶς τε καὶ εὖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.59, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1103; Σπάρτην ἔλαχες, κείνην κόσμει 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 723 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἐμαυτόν <b>restrain</b> myself, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Hyps.fragment” 34(60).46; τὰ ἄλλα ἐκεκοσμέατό οἱ 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.100; τόν γε νοῦν κοσμοῦντα πάντα κοσμεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 97 c:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, τὰ κοσμούμενα <b>orderly institutions</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 677 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <i>participle</i>, of persons, <b>orderly</b>, ταπεινὸς καὶ κεκοσμημένος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 716a; τεταγμένον τε καὶ κ. πρᾶγμα [prev. author] “Grg.” 504 a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> in Crete, <b>hold office of</b> κόσμος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 111, οἱ κεκοσμηκότες 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1272a35, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 22.15.1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; Cretan dialect <b>κοσμίω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Leg.Gort.” 1.51, etc.\">Refs</a>]; also κορμίω (which see). <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>adorn, equip, dress</b>, especially of women, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hymni Homerici” 6.11, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 72; κοσμῆσαί τινα πανοπλίῃ 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.180; τριπόδεσσι κ. δόμον 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 1.19; τινὰ πλούτῳ ὑπερβάλλοντι 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 3.10.6: with double _accusative_, πρίν σε νυμφικὸν ἰστέφανον κοσμήσαμεν “JRS” 17.51 (Phrygia, 4th c.AD):—frequently in \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>middle</i>, κοσμέεσθαι τὰς κεφαλάς <b>to adorn their</b> heads, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.209; κοσμεῖσθαι σῶμα ὅπλοις 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1359 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν φοινικίσι κοσμησάμενοι having decked themselves who roasts [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 208 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, χρυσῷ κοσμηθεῖσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Venerem” 65; παῖσα δ᾽ Ἄρῃ κεκόσμηται στέγα 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 15.1; ἵπποι κεκοσμημένοι ὡς κάλλιστα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.40; κεκ. ἐσθῆτι ποικίλῃ καὶ χρυσοῖσι στεφάνοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ion” 535 d, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1064, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.41, etc. \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>adorn, embellish</b>, λόγους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 576; λόγους ῥήμασί τε καὶ ὀνόμασι κεκοσμημένους 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 17 c; τραγικὸν λῆρον 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1005 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἔργον ἄριστον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 1027; τὸ λογικὸν ἔχεις ἐξαίρετον, τοῦτο κόσμει 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 3.1.26; λόγον εὐρυθμίαις 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 5.27; αὑτὸν λόγοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 196 b, compare 197 c; ἐπὶ τὸ μεῖζον κ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.21 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν.. τὴν ἐκείνων ἀρετὴν κοσμήσοντα (in speaking) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.287 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ἦθος σεμνότητι -μημένον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “Academicorum Index” p.52 M. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <b>honour</b>, λουτροῖς σ᾽ ἐκόσμης᾽ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1139; κ. τάφον [prev. author] “Ant.” 396; νέκυν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 1147; κ. καὶ τιμᾶν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.3.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of persons, <b>adorn, be an honour to</b>, πατρίδα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 947; νᾶσον εὐκλέα 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 6.46; Σαλαμῖνα κ. πατρίδα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 530.3; [τὴν πόλιν] αἱ τῶνδε ἀρεταὶ ἐκόσμησαν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.42. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.4</b></Level3> <b>bury</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “JHS” 25.172, +others (from Isauria). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be assigned, ascribed to</b>, ἐς τὸν Αἰγύπτιον νομὸν αὗται [αἱ πόλεις] ἐκεκοσμέατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.91; ἐς Πέρσας κεκοσμέαται [prev. author] 6.41 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially of philosophic schools, κατὰ τὴν Ἀκαδημίαν κοσμεῖσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “Πυρρώνειοι ὑποτυπώσεις” 1.231; οἱ κατὰ διαφόρους αἱρέσεις κοσμούμενοι [prev. author] “M.” 11.77. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2885","accentedUnicode":"κοσμέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2889","matchingForm":"κόσμος","stepTransliteration":"kosmos","gloss":"world","_zh_tw_Gloss":"世界","_es_Gloss":"mundo","_zh_Gloss":"世界"}],"shortDef":"to make beautiful, decorate, dress; trim (a lamp); (<i>passive</i>) to put in order; be adorned, decorated, beautifully dressed arrange","mediumDef":"to make beautiful, decorate, dress; trim (a lamp); (<i>passive</i>) to put in order; be adorned, decorated, beautifully dressed arrange <br />pluperfect, <greek>ἐκεκόσμητο</greek> (3 <i>singular</i>), <b>to arrange, set